<br>
Underpaid is a relative term. If you believe they are underpaid in an &quot;economic&quot; sense, then that wouldn't be the case. In the most extreme economics, no one is underpaid (and no one is overpaid). Supply of labour will equal the demand for labour. <br>
<br>
Look at the amount of people applying for teachers college. It's mind boggling. That's why teachers salaries are so low.<br>
<br>
Why are lawyers salaries so high? Because they restrict entry by BAR exams etc, and restrict the entrance of lawyers into the field.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I should have control over the spending of money that I EARN. This whole working for your money concept is really just beyond your capacity, isn’t it? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If everyone has control over every dollar they earn, then there's gonna be a heck of a lot of people who are starving to death. Re-distrubtion of income is a necessaity. And not only does it have economic benefits, it also has cultural, social, and demographic benefits as well.<br>
